<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="265" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,376]" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Filho, 2017" authorityName="Souza-Filho" authorityYear="2017" box="[324,566,151,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischnomesidae" genus="Ischnomesus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,566,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">Ischnomesus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[576,668,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[576,668,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a pattern of ornamentation similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Merrin &amp; Poore, 2003" authorityName="Merrin &amp; Poore" authorityYear="2003" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischnomesidae" genus="Ischnomesus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tasmanensis">
<emphasis box="[1155,1318,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">I. tasmanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Merrin" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" refString="Merrin, K. &amp; Poore, G. C. B. (2003) Four new species of Ischnomesidae (Crustacea: Isopoda: Asellota) from off south-eastern Australia. Memoirs of Museum Fictoria, 60, 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2003.60.27" type="journal article" year="2003">Merrin &amp; Poore, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The positioning of anterolateral spine, on pereonite I, and dorsal spines, on pereonites I–IV, observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrin &amp; Poore" authorityYear="2003" box="[180,340,220,243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischnomesidae" genus="Ischnomesus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tasmanensis">
<emphasis box="[180,340,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">I. tasmanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the same position of the pedestal spine and pedestal setae observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza-Filho, 2017" authorityName="Souza-Filho" authorityYear="2017" box="[1156,1395,218,243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischnomesidae" genus="Ischnomesus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1156,1395,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">Ischnomesus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="265" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, respectively. However, this species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrin &amp; Poore" authorityYear="2003" box="[752,913,253,276]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischnomesidae" genus="Ischnomesus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tasmanensis">
<emphasis box="[752,913,253,276]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="265">I. tasmanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by pleotelson: spines, format and lateral fields bulge in pleotelson, never reported before.
</paragraph>
